<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/266: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frost</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-04T17:00:00-04:00">March 4, 1938—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>30. Department’s 17, February 14, 6 p.m. Foreign Office states it will
                            begin conversations with Embassy on trade agreement early next week,
                            having its proposals now at last rough drafted.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>